Package edu.vt.cbil.visda.view

provides the VISDA GUI and Visualization Modules

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
IViewer The interface of a class, which can be displayed in the framework scroll pane.
 

Class Summary
AnnotationDialog The class is used to generate the dialog for sample annotation
ClusterResultsViewer The class to add the results of one certain level into the view tree
ConfigDialog The class is to configure main parameteres used in VISDA analysis
DataPreViewer The class to view the data after pre-processing
DisplayParam The class contains all the parameters for display
FeaturePreViewer The class to view the selected features after pre-processing
GBA  
HistoryViewer The class to view history log
LeafInfo This class is a structure, which is used to assign properties for a tree node.
LevelResultsViewer The class to add the results of one certain level into the view tree
MainViewer The class to generate the main view tree
MDLDialog The class is used to let user choose the optimum number of sub-clusters for one class
MDLPanel The class is used to plot the MDL values
MultiPlotsViewer The class to view multiple 2D-projection plots at a window
MultiProj2DClickDialog The class is used to let user choose center pointers with mouse-click for multiple clusters on the same level
Plot2DViewer The class is used to plot one single 2D projection combined the Posterior probabilities of samples
Proj2DClickDialog The class is used to let user choose center pointers with mouse-click for one cluster
Proj2DClickPanel The class is used to let user choose center pointers with mouse-click on 2D projection plot
ProjSelectionDialog The class is used to generate the dialog for projection type selection
ProjSelectionPanel The class is used to generate the panel for projection type selection
RawDataViewer The class to view Raw DataSet
TableViewer The class to view data with table
ViewerAdapter The class to view history log
